Epigynal field with discontinuous anterior bands. Lateral lobes (LL) widely separated from each other. Median septum (MS) wide, covered partly by lateral lobes medially and posteriorly. Internal duct system with anterior part of first winding medially touching each other, looped apex rounded, situated at the margin of the first winding, posteriolaterad. Spermathecae large and oval, separated from each other by their diameter. Fertilization ducts (FD) arising posterio-medially, laterad (
Figs 1D–E
).
